(2:08) I met so many new people and they were
all extremely nice.

00:02:14.119 --> 00:02:16.370
(2:14) I love the city of Lexington.

00:02:16.370 --> 00:02:20.940
I love that it is sort of smaller because
you could be on campus and then five minutes

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:22.150
later you are downtown.

00:02:22.150 --> 00:02:31.850
It has the different local restaurants, all
the shopping places and then there is Keeneland

00:02:31.850 --> 00:02:33.980
watching the races...green grass and the horses.

00:02:33.980 --> 00:02:34.980
It's a beautiful place.

00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:36.300
(2:35) There's so much to do.

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:39.400
There is just always something for you to
get involved with.

00:02:39.400 --> 00:02:42.190
(2:39) From the beginning I got involved with
undergraduate research.

00:02:42.190 --> 00:02:48.910
All of a sudden I'm working in the lab of
a world-renowned professor and I'm just a

00:02:48.910 --> 00:02:49.910
freshman.

00:02:49.910 --> 00:02:51.250
(2:48) Research opportunities here at UK are
incredible.

00:02:51.250 --> 00:02:53.750
They are something you are really not going
to find anywhere else.

00:02:53.750 --> 00:02:58.150
(2:53) We are pretty much breeding these two
fish that have two different genes and seeing

00:02:58.150 --> 00:03:01.530
what happens when we have a fish with both
of those genes.

00:03:01.530 --> 00:03:05.980
